      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.pjhjTVwvrN4Ly9BR]{Isolation}</p>\n<p>As you detach from reality, you ignore some of its limitations and threats. When you enter your @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.q5GZ1Oo5U3VODBpf]{Silent State}, you gain temporary Hit Points equal to your mystic level. These last until your silent state ends. While in your silent state, if your Wisdom modifier is at least 2 higher than the ability score modifier you apply to an attack roll, you gain a +1 insight bonus to the attack roll. Finally, while in your silent state, creatures take a â€“1 penalty to initial saving throws against your mystic spells when those creatures are not within melee reach of any of their allies; this does not apply to spells of the highest spell level that you can cast.</p>"
